<paragraph blockId="24.[813,1420,443,667]" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,974,443,467]" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">Identification.</emphasis>
This species is characterized by its short internodes, fibrous persistent cataphylls, subterete peti- oles (almost as long as the blade), and narrowly ovate blades, which are moderately cordate at base with a hippocrepiform sinus and naked posterior ribs. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Philodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="24" pageNumber="675" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albisuccus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">Philodendron albisuccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species of Cerro Pirre that has whitish sap when cutting its vegetative parts.
</paragraph>
