<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="675" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="24.[813,1420,692,850]" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,1109,692,716]" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[1119,1223,692,716]" name="Colombia" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1283,1372,693,716]" name="Panama" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">Panama</collectingCountry>
. On Cerro Pirre, 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1106,726,750]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Philodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="24" pageNumber="675" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albisuccus">
<emphasis box="[958,1106,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">P. albisuccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ocurrs only in submontane and montane forests, generally above 
<specimenCount box="[1231,1308,759,783]" pageId="24" pageNumber="675" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1231,1304,759,783]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="675" unit="m" value="800.0">800 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
This species grows frequently on trunks and branches located between 
<quantity box="[909,998,825,850]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="675" unit="m" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2 to 5 m</quantity>
high.
</paragraph>
